                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>New York</placeName>. <date>Dec. 9.\n                                                  1847</date>.</p>\n                              <p>To <persName role=\"author\">Uriah H. Judah Esq.</persName></p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(3)\">Sir,</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(4)\">The following<lb/> questions appear to me to\n                                        involve a subject of most<lb/> deep and peculiar interest,\n                                        not only to ourselves in-<lb/>dividually, but to the whole\n                                        religious community.<lb/> These questions are addressed to\n                                        you under the im-<lb/>pression that your acknowledged\n                                        respectability of<lb/> character and liberality of views\n                                        will prompt you<lb/> to answer them.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">1st. Is it not <hi rend=\"underline\"\n                                                  >peculiarly</hi> the spirit and priv-<lb/>ilege\n                                        and work of Judaism to spread among<lb/> idolatrous nations,\n                                        the knowledge of the true God, and the records of His\n                                        communion with<lb/>\n                                        <persName>Abraham</persName>\n                                        <persName>Isaac</persName> and <persName>Jacob</persName>\n                                        and all the ancient<lb/> prophets?</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">2nd. Does the Christian enterprise of universal\n                                        Bible<lb/> distribution commend itself to the Jewish<lb/>\n                                        community? Or</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">3d. Are there such features in either the\n                                        nature<lb/> or the invariably accompanying\n                                        circumstances<lb/> of the Christian religious enterprises,\n                                        as necessarily<lb/> shut out the Jew from all participation,\n                                        and leave<lb/> no conceivable ground of benevolent union\n                                        between<lb/> Jew and Christian, except the broad</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3j679p1v/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
